.TH "vmballoon_deflate" 9 "vmballoon_deflate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmballoon_deflate \- Decrease the size of the balloon.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" vmballoon_deflate
.BI "(struct vmballoon *b "  ","
.BI "uint64_t n_frames "  ","
.BI "bool coordinated "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "b" 12
pointer to the balloon
.IP "n_frames" 12
the number of frames to deflate. If zero, automatically
calculated according to the target size.
.IP "coordinated" 12
whether to coordinate with the host
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Decrease the size of the balloon allowing guest to use more memory.
.SH "RETURN"
The number of deflated frames (i.e., basic page size units)
